import React, { useState } from "react"; import { Grid, Paper, Button, Drawer, List, ListItem, Typography, IconButton, Card, CardMedia } from "@material-ui/core"; import '@fontsource/roboto'; import ProfilePic from "../krystal.png"; import MidwifePic from "../midwife1.png"; const About = () => { const style = { font: { color: "#454545", margin: 20, fontSize: 25 }, font2: { color: "#630070", margin: 20, fontSize: 18, }, font3: { color: "black", fontSize: 30, borderBottom: "3px solid #630070", borderRight: "3px solid #630070", backgroundColor: "lightpink", margin: 20, borderRadius: 20 }, picture: { width: "80%", height: "auto", marginTop: 40, borderRadius: 180, border: "3px solid #F6CBFF" }, picture2: { width: "40%", height: "auto" }, title: { marginBottom: "5%", color: "#454545" }, section: { marginTop: "5%" }, card: { padding: 50, backgroundColor: "#FFCFED", marginBottom: 50 }, card2: { padding: 10, margin: 15 } } return ( Krystal Smith, MSN, APRN, CNM My mission is to support physiologic pregnancy and birth by providing safe and evidence-based midwifery care in the home setting. Pregnancy and birth bring forth sacred and beautiful physiologic moments for which should be protected through physical and emotional support. We will work together through informed consent and shared decision making so you can feel confident in the decisions about your pregnancy and birth. My hope is for you to feel supported, empowered, and to ultimately love your birth experience. {/* What Care Is Provided? -Antenatal home visits Labor and birth care in the home Postpartum care home visits Newborn care home visits up to 28 days of life */}
Experience Master’s degree in the Science of Nurse-Midwifery Registered Nurse in Labor & Delivery and Postpartum for 5.5 years Midwifery Clinical experience in the home setting Neonatal resuscitation certified BLS CPR certified
Interests Supporting physiologic birth Breastfeeding Shared decision making Evidence-based care Informed consent Supporting women’s desires Family centered care
) } export default About;
